            "explanation": "The main accessibility issue is the lack of ARIA live regions to announce step changes for screen reader users. When steps change dynamically, screen readers need to be notified of the context change.\n\n[CODE]// Accessible multi-step form implementation\n<form id=\"multiStepForm\" aria-labelledby=\"form-title\">\n  <h1 id=\"form-title\" class=\"sr-only\">Multi-step Registration Form</h1>\n  \n  <!-- Progress indicator -->\n  <div role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Form progress\">\n    <ol class=\"progress-steps\">\n      <li aria-current=\"step\">Personal Information</li>\n      <li>Contact Details</li>\n      <li>Confirmation</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  \n  <!-- Live region for announcements -->\n  <div \n    id=\"form-announcer\" \n    aria-live=\"polite\" \n    aria-atomic=\"true\"\n    class=\"sr-only\">\n  </div>\n  \n  <div \n    class=\"step\" \n    id=\"step1\" \n    role=\"region\" \n    aria-labelledby=\"step1-title\">\n    \n    <h2 id=\"step1-title\">Personal Information</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n      <label for=\"name\">Full Name</label>\n      <input \n        type=\"text\" \n        id=\"name\" \n        name=\"name\" \n        required\n        aria-required=\"true\">\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-actions\">\n      <button \n        type=\"button\" \n        onclick=\"showStep(2)\"\n        aria-describedby=\"step1-instructions\">\n        Next: Contact Details\n      </button>\n    </div>\n    \n    <p id=\"step1-instructions\" class=\"sr-only\">\n      Press enter to continue to contact details\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div \n    class=\"step\" \n    id=\"step2\" \n    hidden \n    role=\"region\" \n    aria-labelledby=\"step2-title\">\n    \n    <h2 id=\"step2-title\">Contact Details</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n      <label for=\"email\">Email Address</label>\n      <input \n        type=\"email\" \n        id=\"email\" \n        name=\"email\" \n        required\n        aria-required=\"true\">\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-actions\">\n      <button \n        type=\"button\" \n        onclick=\"showStep(1)\"\n        aria-describedby=\"step2-back-instructions\">\n        Back to Personal Information\n      </button>\n      \n      <button \n        type=\"submit\"\n        aria-describedby=\"step2-submit-instructions\">\n        Submit Registration\n      </button>\n    </div>\n    \n    <p id=\"step2-back-instructions\" class=\"sr-only\">\n      Press enter to return to personal information\n    </p>\n    <p id=\"step2-submit-instructions\" class=\"sr-only\">\n      Press enter to submit your registration\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</form>\n\n<script>\nfunction showStep(stepNumber) {\n  const currentStep = document.querySelector('.step:not([hidden])');\n  const targetStep = document.getElementById(`step${stepNumber}`);\n  const announcer = document.getElementById('form-announcer');\n  \n  if (currentStep && targetStep) {\n    // Update progress indicator\n    updateProgress(stepNumber);\n    \n    // Hide current step\n    currentStep.hidden = true;\n    currentStep.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');\n    \n    // Show target step\n    targetStep.hidden = false;\n    targetStep.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'false');\n    \n    // Focus first focusable element in new step\n    const firstInput = targetStep.querySelector('input, button, select, textarea');\n    if (firstInput) {\n      firstInput.focus();\n    }\n    \n    // Announce step change\n    const stepTitle = targetStep.querySelector('h2').textContent;\n    announcer.textContent = `Now showing: ${stepTitle}`;\n    \n    // Update current step in progress\n    document.querySelectorAll('.progress-steps li').forEach((li, index) => {\n      if (index + 1 === stepNumber) {\n        li.setAttribute('aria-current', 'step');\n      } else {\n        li.removeAttribute('aria-current');\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction updateProgress(currentStep) {\n  const progressItems = document.querySelectorAll('.progress-steps li');\n  \n  progressItems.forEach((item, index) => {\n    const stepNum = index + 1;\n    \n    if (stepNum < currentStep) {\n      item.className = 'completed';\n    } else if (stepNum === currentStep) {\n      item.className = 'current';\n    } else {\n      item.className = 'upcoming';\n    }\n  });\n}\n</script>[/CODE]\n\nDynamic form steps require careful accessibility consideration to ensure all users can understand and navigate the form progression.",
