            "question": "What accessibility improvement is needed in this tab interface implementation?\n[CODE]<div class=\"tabs\">\n  <div class=\"tab-headers\">\n    <button class=\"tab-header active\" onclick=\"showTab(1)\">Description</button>\n    <button class=\"tab-header\" onclick=\"showTab(2)\">Specifications</button>\n    <button class=\"tab-header\" onclick=\"showTab(3)\">Reviews</button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"tab-content\">\n    <div class=\"tab-panel active\" id=\"tab1\">\n      <h3>Product Description</h3>\n      <p>Detailed product description...</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"tab-panel\" id=\"tab2\" hidden>\n      <h3>Specifications</h3>\n      <p>Technical specifications...</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"tab-panel\" id=\"tab3\" hidden>\n      <h3>Customer Reviews</h3>\n      <p>Review content...</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nfunction showTab(tabNumber) {\n  // Hide all panels\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {\n    panel.hidden = true;\n  });\n  \n  // Remove active class from all headers\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-header').forEach(header => {\n    header.classList.remove('active');\n  });\n  \n  // Show selected panel and activate header\n  document.getElementById(`tab${tabNumber}`).hidden = false;\n  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-header')[tabNumber - 1].classList.add('active');\n}\n</script>[/CODE]",
            "options": {
                "A": "Missing ARIA roles and keyboard navigation",
                "B": "Incorrect use of hidden attribute",
                "C": "No focus management between tabs",
                "D": "All of the above"
            },
            "correct": "D",
            "explanation": "This tab implementation lacks several key accessibility features: proper ARIA roles, keyboard navigation support, and focus management. Screen reader users and keyboard-only users cannot properly interact with the tabs.\n\n[CODE]// Accessible tab interface implementation\n<div class=\"tabs\" role=\"tablist\" aria-label=\"Product information\">\n  <div class=\"tab-headers\">\n    <button \n      role=\"tab\"\n      aria-selected=\"true\"\n      aria-controls=\"tab1\"\n      id=\"tab1-header\"\n      class=\"tab-header active\"\n      tabindex=\"0\"\n      onclick=\"showTab(1)\"\n      onkeydown=\"handleTabKey(event, 1)\">\n      Description\n    </button>\n    \n    <button \n      role=\"tab\"\n      aria-selected=\"false\"\n      aria-controls=\"tab2\"\n      id=\"tab2-header\"\n      class=\"tab-header\"\n      tabindex=\"-1\"\n      onclick=\"showTab(2)\"\n      onkeydown=\"handleTabKey(event, 2)\">\n      Specifications\n    </button>\n    \n    <button \n      role=\"tab\"\n      aria-selected=\"false\"\n      aria-controls=\"tab3\"\n      id=\"tab3-header\"\n      class=\"tab-header\"\n      tabindex=\"-1\"\n      onclick=\"showTab(3)\"\n      onkeydown=\"handleTabKey(event, 3)\">\n      Reviews\n    </button>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"tab-content\">\n    <div \n      role=\"tabpanel\"\n      id=\"tab1\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"tab1-header\"\n      class=\"tab-panel active\"\n      tabindex=\"0\">\n      \n      <h3>Product Description</h3>\n      <p>Detailed product description...</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div \n      role=\"tabpanel\"\n      id=\"tab2\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"tab2-header\"\n      class=\"tab-panel\" \n      hidden\n      tabindex=\"0\">\n      \n      <h3>Specifications</h3>\n      <p>Technical specifications...</p>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div \n      role=\"tabpanel\"\n      id=\"tab3\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"tab3-header\"\n      class=\"tab-panel\" \n      hidden\n      tabindex=\"0\">\n      \n      <h3>Customer Reviews</h3>\n      <p>Review content...</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nlet currentTab = 1;\nconst totalTabs = 3;\n\nfunction showTab(tabNumber) {\n  // Update ARIA attributes for tabs\n  document.querySelectorAll('[role=\"tab\"]').forEach((tab, index) => {\n    const isSelected = index + 1 === tabNumber;\n    tab.setAttribute('aria-selected', isSelected);\n    tab.setAttribute('tabindex', isSelected ? '0' : '-1');\n    tab.classList.toggle('active', isSelected);\n  });\n  \n  // Update tab panels\n  document.querySelectorAll('[role=\"tabpanel\"]').forEach((panel, index) => {\n    const isVisible = index + 1 === tabNumber;\n    panel.hidden = !isVisible;\n  });\n  \n  currentTab = tabNumber;\n  \n  // Focus the activated tab for keyboard users\n  document.getElementById(`tab${tabNumber}-header`).focus();\n}\n\nfunction handleTabKey(event, tabNumber) {\n  switch(event.key) {\n    case 'ArrowRight':\n      event.preventDefault();\n      showTab(tabNumber < totalTabs ? tabNumber + 1 : 1);\n      break;\n      \n    case 'ArrowLeft':\n      event.preventDefault();\n      showTab(tabNumber > 1 ? tabNumber - 1 : totalTabs);\n      break;\n      \n    case 'Home':\n      event.preventDefault();\n      showTab(1);\n      break;\n      \n    case 'End':\n      event.preventDefault();\n      showTab(totalTabs);\n      break;\n  }\n}\n\n// Initialize tabs\ndocument.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {\n  showTab(1);\n});\n</script>\n\n<style>\n.tab-header {\n  padding: 12px 24px;\n  border: none;\n  background: #f7fafc;\n  cursor: pointer;\n}\n\n.tab-header.active,\n.tab-header[aria-selected=\"true\"] {\n  background: #4299e1;\n  color: white;\n}\n\n.tab-header:focus {\n  outline: 2px solid #4299e1;\n  outline-offset: 2px;\n}\n\n.tab-panel {\n  padding: 16px;\n  border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n}\n\n.tab-panel:focus {\n  outline: 2px solid #4299e1;\n}\n</style>[/CODE]\n\nAccessible tab interfaces require proper ARIA roles, keyboard navigation, and focus management to be usable by all people, including those using assistive technologies.",
