            "question": "What is the purpose of the <pre>meta</pre> tags in this document head?\n[CODE]<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Premium wireless headphones with noise cancellation technology.\">\n  <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"headphones, wireless, audio, noise cancellation\">\n  <meta name=\"author\" content=\"AudioTech Inc.\">\n  \n  <!-- Open Graph -->\n  <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Premium Wireless Headphones\">\n  <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Experience crystal clear audio with our noise-cancelling wireless headphones.\">\n  <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://example.com/images/headphones-social.jpg\">\n  <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://example.com/products/headphones\">\n  <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"product\">\n  \n  <!-- Twitter Card -->\n  <meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"Premium Wireless Headphones\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"Experience crystal clear audio with noise cancellation.\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:image\" content=\"https://example.com/images/headphones-twitter.jpg\">\n  \n  <!-- Additional meta tags -->\n  <meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow\">\n  <meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#1a202c\">\n  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n</head>[/CODE]",
            "options": {
                "A": "They enable JavaScript functionality",
                "B": "They control page styling and layout",
                "C": "They provide document metadata for browsers, SEO, and social media",
                "D": "They compress page resources"
            },
            "correct": "C",
            "explanation": "The <pre>meta</pre> tags provide essential document metadata for browsers, search engines, and social media platforms. They control how the page is displayed, indexed, and shared across different platforms.\n\n[CODE]// Comprehensive meta tag strategy\n\n// 1. Essential meta tags\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"> <!-- Character encoding -->\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"> <!-- Responsive design -->\n\n// 2. SEO meta tags\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Concise, compelling page description (150-160 characters)\">\n<meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"relevant, comma, separated, keywords\"> <!-- Less important now -->\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Company or Author Name\">\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow\"> <!-- Search engine instructions -->\n\n// 3. Open Graph (Facebook, LinkedIn, etc.)\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Page Title\">\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Engaging social media description\">\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://example.com/social-image.jpg\">\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://example.com/page-url\">\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\"> <!-- website, article, product, etc. -->\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Site Name\">\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\">\n\n// 4. Twitter Card\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\"> <!-- summary, summary_large_image, app, player -->\n<meta name=\"twitter:site\" content=\"@username\">\n<meta name=\"twitter:creator\" content=\"@author\">\n<meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"Page Title\">\n<meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"Twitter-optimized description\">\n<meta name=\"twitter:image\" content=\"https://example.com/twitter-image.jpg\">\n\n// 5. Additional important meta tags\n<meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#color\"> <!-- Browser theme color -->\n<meta name=\"msapplication-TileColor\" content=\"#color\"> <!-- Windows tile color -->\n<meta name=\"apple-mobile-web-app-capable\" content=\"yes\"> <!-- PWA support -->\n<meta name=\"apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style\" content=\"default\">\n\n// 6. Security and performance\n<meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\"> <!-- Force latest IE mode -->\n<meta name=\"referrer\" content=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\"> <!-- Referrer policy -->\n\n// 7. Verification and ownership\n<meta name=\"google-site-verification\" content=\"verification_token\">\n<meta name=\"facebook-domain-verification\" content=\"verification_token\">\n\n// 8. Structured data in meta tags (alternative to JSON-LD)\n<meta itemprop=\"name\" content=\"Product Name\">\n<meta itemprop=\"description\" content=\"Product description\">\n<meta itemprop=\"image\" content=\"https://example.com/product.jpg\">\n\n// Dynamic meta tags based on content\n<script>\n// Update meta tags dynamically for single-page applications\nfunction updateMetaTags(pageData) {\n  const metaTags = {\n    title: pageData.title,\n    description: pageData.description,\n    image: pageData.image,\n    url: pageData.url\n  };\n  \n  // Update standard meta tags\n  document.title = metaTags.title;\n  document.querySelector('meta[name=\"description\"]').content = metaTags.description;\n  \n  // Update Open Graph tags\n  document.querySelector('meta[property=\"og:title\"]').content = metaTags.title;\n  document.querySelector('meta[property=\"og:description\"]').content = metaTags.description;\n  document.querySelector('meta[property=\"og:image\"]').content = metaTags.image;\n  document.querySelector('meta[property=\"og:url\"]').content = metaTags.url;\n  \n  // Update Twitter Card tags\n  document.querySelector('meta[name=\"twitter:title\"]').content = metaTags.title;\n  document.querySelector('meta[name=\"twitter:description\"]').content = metaTags.description;\n  document.querySelector('meta[name=\"twitter:image\"]').content = metaTags.image;\n}\n\n// Example usage\nupdateMetaTags({\n  title: \"Dynamic Page Title\",\n  description: \"Dynamic page description for SEO and social sharing\",\n  image: \"https://example.com/dynamic-image.jpg\",\n  url: window.location.href\n});\n</script>\n\n// Meta tags for different page types\n\n// Article page\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\">\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2024-01-16T14:30:00Z\">\n<meta property=\"article:author\" content=\"Author Name\">\n<meta property=\"article:section\" content=\"Technology\">\n<meta property=\"article:tag\" content=\"HTML, Meta Tags, SEO\">\n\n// Product page\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"product\">\n<meta property=\"product:price:amount\" content=\"99.99\">\n<meta property=\"product:price:currency\" content=\"USD\">\n<meta property=\"product:availability\" content=\"in stock\">\n\n// Business page\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"business.business\">\n<meta property=\"business:contact_data:street_address\" content=\"123 Main St\">\n<meta property=\"business:contact_data:locality\" content=\"City\">\n<meta property=\"business:contact_data:region\" content=\"State\">\n<meta property=\"business:contact_data:postal_code\" content=\"12345\">\n<meta property=\"business:contact_data:country_name\" content=\"USA\">[/CODE]\n\nProper meta tag implementation is crucial for SEO, social media sharing, and ensuring your content is properly displayed and indexed across different platforms and devices.",
