            "id": 8,
            "question": "What is the semantic purpose of the <pre>time</pre> element with datetime attribute in this article?\n[CODE]<article>\n  <header>\n    <h1>Understanding Web Accessibility</h1>\n    \n    <div class=\"article-meta\">\n      <address class=\"author\">By \n        <a rel=\"author\" href=\"/author/jane-smith\">Jane Smith</a>\n      </address>\n      \n      <time \n        datetime=\"2024-01-15T14:30:00Z\" \n        title=\"January 15, 2024 at 2:30 PM\">\n        January 15, 2024\n      </time>\n      \n      <time \n        datetime=\"2024-01-20T10:00:00Z\" \n        class=\"updated\"\n        aria-label=\"Last updated: January 20, 2024\">\n        Updated: 5 days ago\n      </time>\n    </div>\n  </header>\n  \n  <div class=\"article-content\">\n    <p>Web accessibility ensures that websites are usable by people with disabilities...</p>\n    \n    <p>Published on \n      <time datetime=\"2024-01-15\">January 15th</time> \n      and last updated on \n      <time datetime=\"2024-01-20\">January 20th</time>.\n    </p>\n    \n    <footer>\n      <p>Article length: \n        <time datetime=\"PT5M\">5 minute read</time>\n      </p>\n    </footer>\n  </div>\n</article>[/CODE]",
            "options": {
                "A": "It enables date-based CSS styling",
                "B": "It automatically formats dates for different locales",
                "C": "It improves page loading performance",
                "D": "It provides machine-readable datetime information while displaying human-readable text"
            },
            "correct": "D",
            "explanation": "The <pre>time</pre> element with datetime attribute provides machine-readable datetime information (for search engines, browsers, and scripts) while displaying human-readable text to users. This enables better semantic understanding and potential automation.\n\n[CODE]// Comprehensive time element usage\n\n// 1. Basic date and time\n<time datetime=\"2024-01-15\">January 15, 2024</time>\n<time datetime=\"14:30\">2:30 PM</time>\n<time datetime=\"2024-01-15T14:30:00Z\">January 15, 2024 at 2:30 PM UTC</time>\n\n// 2. Relative times with precise datetime\n<time datetime=\"2024-01-15T14:30:00Z\" title=\"January 15, 2024\">\n  3 days ago\n</time>\n\n// 3. Durations\n<time datetime=\"PT2H30M\">2 hours 30 minutes</time>\n<time datetime=\"P3D\">3 days</time>\n<time datetime=\"P1Y6M\">1 year 6 months</time>\n\n// 4. Event scheduling\n<div class=\"event\">\n  <h3>Web Development Conference</h3>\n  \n  <p>\n    Starts: \n    <time datetime=\"2024-03-15T09:00:00-05:00\">\n      March 15, 2024 at 9:00 AM EST\n    </time>\n  </p>\n  \n  <p>\n    Ends: \n    <time datetime=\"2024-03-17T17:00:00-05:00\">\n      March 17, 2024 at 5:00 PM EST\n    </time>\n  </p>\n  \n  <p>\n    Duration: \n    <time datetime=\"P3D\">3 days</time>\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n// 5. Opening hours with microdata\n<div itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Restaurant\">\n  <h3 itemprop=\"name\">Coffee Shop</h3>\n  \n  <div itemprop=\"openingHours\" content=\"Mo-Fr 07:00-19:00\">\n    Weekdays: \n    <time datetime=\"07:00\">7:00 AM</time> - \n    <time datetime=\"19:00\">7:00 PM</time>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div itemprop=\"openingHours\" content=\"Sa-Su 08:00-17:00\">\n    Weekends: \n    <time datetime=\"08:00\">8:00 AM</time> - \n    <time datetime=\"17:00\">5:00 PM</time>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n// 6. Historical dates\n<article>\n  <h2>Historical Event</h2>\n  \n  <p>\n    The event occurred on \n    <time datetime=\"1969-07-20\">July 20, 1969</time> \n    at approximately \n    <time datetime=\"20:17\">8:17 PM</time>.\n  </p>\n  \n  <p>\n    This was \n    <time datetime=\"P54Y\">54 years</time> ago.\n  </p>\n</article>\n\n// 7. Countdown timer\n<div class=\"countdown\" data-target=\"2024-12-31T23:59:59Z\">\n  <p>\n    New Year in: \n    <time datetime=\"P90D\">90 days</time>\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n// JavaScript for dynamic time handling\nclass TimeFormatter {\n  // Format relative time\n  static formatRelative(datetime) {\n    const now = new Date();\n    const target = new Date(datetime);\n    const diff = target - now;\n    \n    const days = Math.floor(diff / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24));\n    const hours = Math.floor((diff % (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24)) / (1000 * 60 * 60));\n    \n    if (days > 0) {\n      return `in ${days} day${days !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`;\n    } else if (hours > 0) {\n      return `in ${hours} hour${hours !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`;\n    } else {\n      return 'soon';\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Update relative times periodically\n  static updateRelativeTimes() {\n    document.querySelectorAll('time[datetime]').forEach(timeElement => {\n      const datetime = timeElement.getAttribute('datetime');\n      \n      // Check if it's a future date\n      if (this.isFutureDate(datetime)) {\n        const relativeText = this.formatRelative(datetime);\n        \n        // Only update if text has changed\n        if (timeElement.textContent !== relativeText) {\n          timeElement.textContent = relativeText;\n        }\n      }\n    });\n  }\n  \n  static isFutureDate(datetime) {\n    return new Date(datetime) > new Date();\n  }\n}\n\n// Update relative times every minute\nsetInterval(() => {\n  TimeFormatter.updateRelativeTimes();\n}, 60000);\n\n// Initialize on page load\ndocument.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n  TimeFormatter.updateRelativeTimes();\n});\n\n// CSS for time elements\ntime {\n  font-weight: 500;\n}\n\ntime.updated {\n  color: #718096;\n  font-size: 0.9em;\n}\n\n/* Style based on datetime */\ntime[datetime*=\"T09:\"]::before {\n  content: \"ðŸŒ… \";\n}\n\ntime[datetime*=\"T18:\"]::after {\n  content: \" ðŸŒ‡\";\n}\n\n/* Responsive time formatting */\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  time {\n    display: block;\n    margin: 4px 0;\n  }\n}\n\n// Schema.org integration with time\n<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"Article\",\n  \"headline\": \"Understanding Web Accessibility\",\n  \"datePublished\": \"2024-01-15T14:30:00Z\",\n  \"dateModified\": \"2024-01-20T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"timeRequired\": \"PT5M\",\n  \"author\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Person\",\n    \"name\": \"Jane Smith\"\n  }\n}\n</script>[/CODE]\n\nThe <pre>time</pre> element bridges the gap between human-readable date displays and machine-processable datetime information, enabling better semantic markup, improved accessibility, and enhanced search engine understanding.",
